Architecture plan for Issue #109: Enlarge the upper-left TLHN header logo

Current structure:
- frontend/src/App.tsx defines the React SPA shell, including AppShell and the upper-left TLHN header wordmark link around lines 104-110.
- frontend/src/styles.css contains reusable TLHN visual-system classes for the shell, navigation, landing logo, panels, and responsive layout.
- shared/src/index.ts exports PRODUCT_SHORT_NAME = "TLHN", which the header wordmark already renders.
- backend/ and database-related files are unaffected; this is a frontend-only presentation change.

Issue dependencies:
- No dependency on other issues. The request is isolated to the small header wordmark and must not alter the large landing-page neon logo styles (.tlhn-neon-logo).

Key design decisions:
- Keep the existing AppShell link, route behavior, terminal font, uppercase styling, hater color, and glow.
- Increase only the header wordmark text size from text-sm to a responsive size such as text-lg sm:text-xl directly on the existing className in frontend/src/App.tsx.
- Avoid introducing new assets, dependencies, global CSS, or layout restructuring; the nav/header already supports a larger left-aligned mark.
- Validate with the existing frontend TypeScript/build tooling after implementation.
